00:30:27.310 --> 00:30:30.610
I would say some of the advice
I gave him was the following.

00:30:30.610 --> 00:30:31.870
One piece was this.

00:30:31.870 --> 00:30:34.630
We spend the first half
of our life accumulating,

00:30:34.630 --> 00:30:37.300
and we spend the second
half of our life editing.

00:30:37.300 --> 00:30:38.460
That's my point of view.

00:30:38.460 --> 00:30:40.180
And what I mean by
that is you often

00:30:40.180 --> 00:30:41.760
see it with people
with their homes.

00:30:41.760 --> 00:30:44.325
The kids leave, and then,
OK, you want to downsize.

00:30:44.325 --> 00:30:46.450
You see it with people
sometimes with their friends

00:30:46.450 --> 00:30:47.890
and their interests.

00:30:47.890 --> 00:30:50.380
They actually want to get more
focused on certain things,

00:30:50.380 --> 00:30:53.284
because we have stuff,
and we have knowledge,

00:30:53.284 --> 00:30:55.450
and we have all of these
different responsibilities,

00:30:55.450 --> 00:30:59.650
and then around 45 or 50,
we say, this is too much.

00:30:59.650 --> 00:31:01.240
I need to edit it down.

00:31:01.240 --> 00:31:05.800
That editing capability
is really valuable

00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:09.430
when someone younger,
who has a lot of options,

00:31:09.430 --> 00:31:11.479
is able to prioritize.

00:31:11.479 --> 00:31:13.270
One of the things I
think helped Brian with

00:31:13.270 --> 00:31:16.660
was when I joined the
company in early 2013,

00:31:16.660 --> 00:31:19.390
we had 30 strategic initiatives.

00:31:19.390 --> 00:31:21.910
No one in the company,
including Brian,

00:31:21.910 --> 00:31:24.500
could recite the 30
strategic initiatives.

00:31:24.500 --> 00:31:27.790
So I led our off-sites.

00:31:27.790 --> 00:31:30.410
Whenever we did off-sites with
the senior leadership team,

00:31:30.410 --> 00:31:32.950
I usually led those.

00:31:32.950 --> 00:31:36.280
And so our second one
that I led was in New York

00:31:36.280 --> 00:31:38.120
in September of 2013.

00:31:38.120 --> 00:31:40.030
And we had 23
strategic initiatives

00:31:40.030 --> 00:31:42.200
we were going to have for 2014.

00:31:42.200 --> 00:31:43.190
It was sort of nice.

00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:45.120
I said, OK, let's alph--

00:31:45.120 --> 00:31:46.630
put a dozen on the
leadership team.

00:31:46.630 --> 00:31:48.467
Let's come together
and make the decision

00:31:48.467 --> 00:31:50.800
of what are the four that
we're going to actually bet on

00:31:50.800 --> 00:31:51.444
for next year.

00:31:51.444 --> 00:31:53.110
And let's focus on
those, and let's make

00:31:53.110 --> 00:31:55.770
sure everybody in the company
knows those are the four,

00:31:55.770 --> 00:31:59.540
and then we have regular
opportunities for people

00:31:59.540 --> 00:32:01.500
to understand how each
of the four are doing.

00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:03.077
It's so simple,
but honestly, when

00:32:03.077 --> 00:32:05.410
you're in the midst of a
company that's growing and more

00:32:05.410 --> 00:32:07.120
than doubling in
size every year,

00:32:07.120 --> 00:32:09.920
you end up doubling the
number of initiatives.

00:32:09.920 --> 00:32:12.270
So I think prioritization
and editing

00:32:12.270 --> 00:32:16.120
were particularly essential
in my involvement with Brian.

00:32:16.120 --> 00:32:18.130
I think another one
was helping Brian

00:32:18.130 --> 00:32:20.470
understand that the
level of stamina

00:32:20.470 --> 00:32:22.690
that he has as a leader--

00:32:22.690 --> 00:32:24.580
he's a big-- he's just--

00:32:24.580 --> 00:32:27.220
he's a short but stout
and very muscular

00:32:27.220 --> 00:32:30.070
guy who sort of
powers through things.

00:32:30.070 --> 00:32:34.196
And not everyone's like Brian.

00:32:34.196 --> 00:32:35.570
And I think-- I'll
never forget--

00:32:35.570 --> 00:32:37.111
I think it was the
first Thanksgiving

00:32:37.111 --> 00:32:39.480
I was in the company, and
the senior leadership team--

00:32:39.480 --> 00:32:44.130
we've been working,
like, 70, 80 hour weeks.

00:32:44.130 --> 00:32:46.310
And I said to Brian,
like make sure

00:32:46.310 --> 00:32:49.010
that no one talked to each
other over Thanksgiving.

00:32:49.010 --> 00:32:51.140
But also, on Wednesday,
before Thanksgiving

00:32:51.140 --> 00:32:53.645
happens, the day
before Thanksgiving,

00:32:53.645 --> 00:32:56.180
I want you to send
wine, flowers,

00:32:56.180 --> 00:33:00.096
whatever to the spouses
and families of everybody

00:33:00.096 --> 00:33:01.970
who's on the leadership
team, because they're

00:33:01.970 --> 00:33:03.680
the ones who are
at home saying, why

00:33:03.680 --> 00:33:06.510
