00:34:24.980 --> 00:34:28.610
So what I love about
your question, Anonymous,

00:34:28.610 --> 00:34:30.080
is you asked a "why" question.

00:34:32.800 --> 00:34:36.679
One of the things I learned in
my five and 1/2 years at Airbnb

00:34:36.679 --> 00:34:40.219
is that most of the time,
senior leaders and companies

00:34:40.219 --> 00:34:43.670
ask "what" and "how" questions,
which are optimization

00:34:43.670 --> 00:34:47.340
questions, whereas
"why" and "what if"

00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:49.650
are bigger, almost
existential questions.

00:34:49.650 --> 00:34:52.310
They're, frankly, very
inefficient questions,

00:34:52.310 --> 00:34:55.880
because they actually require
a bigger, broader answer.

00:34:55.880 --> 00:34:59.960
And so they're not
all that well-liked

00:34:59.960 --> 00:35:01.730
when they come up in
a meeting, but that's

00:35:01.730 --> 00:35:04.090
what the questions I asked.

00:35:04.090 --> 00:35:06.152
I asked a lot of "why"
and "what if" questions,

00:35:06.152 --> 00:35:07.610
which is, I think,
really valuable,

00:35:07.610 --> 00:35:11.600
because being able to ask these
sort of formative questions

00:35:11.600 --> 00:35:14.120
that might sound
naive, once I realized

00:35:14.120 --> 00:35:18.840
I was an intern as much as I was
a mentor, and I was a learner,

00:35:18.840 --> 00:35:23.030
I could feel comfortable asking
sometimes naive questions.

00:35:23.030 --> 00:35:24.950
So what I would say to the--

00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:27.080
I think that--

00:35:27.080 --> 00:35:29.990
Joe Gebbia and I--
who's the co-founder--

00:35:29.990 --> 00:35:34.359
we did a fireside chat
yesterday at Airbnb.

00:35:34.359 --> 00:35:35.900
And one of the things
we talked about

00:35:35.900 --> 00:35:43.550
was the fact that there's almost
a balancing act for companies

00:35:43.550 --> 00:35:46.550
that grow fast between
scale and soul.

00:35:46.550 --> 00:35:49.430
And that scale and sole
kind of balancing act

00:35:49.430 --> 00:35:53.000
speaks to the scale piece
being very quantifiably

00:35:53.000 --> 00:35:58.240
driven and, often, very much
about what can be proven.

00:35:58.240 --> 00:36:01.220
And the soul piece,
being very intangible,

00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:06.380
often very human-centric,
and, often, more intuitive--

00:36:06.380 --> 00:36:09.440
and to me, the best
companies who get it right

00:36:09.440 --> 00:36:13.610
figure out what's the right
alchemy of scale and soul

00:36:13.610 --> 00:36:15.300
to actually--

00:36:15.300 --> 00:36:17.190
to shoot for in the future.

00:36:17.190 --> 00:36:20.590
And I think the thing
that I said within Airbnb,

00:36:20.590 --> 00:36:23.600
and I tried to lead at Joie
de Vivre, my own company,

00:36:23.600 --> 00:36:25.940
although, frankly, in a bricks
and mortar boutique hotel

00:36:25.940 --> 00:36:27.550
company, we grew
fast, but I mean

00:36:27.550 --> 00:36:33.392
you don't grow like a global
giant like Google or Airbnb.

